  "texts": [
    "Second, the inherent subjectivity and variability in human perception of taste and smell pose major challenges.",
    "Individual differences in genetics, physiology, psychology, and cultural conditioning profoundly affect sensory experiences, complicating the creation of standardized AI models capable of accurately predicting and interpreting sensory data across diverse populations.",
    "Addressing this variability requires personalized or adaptive modeling approaches that integrate individual-level data and account for unique perceptual profiles.",
    "Third, there remains a pronounced lack of standardization in AI-powered sensory evaluations.",
    "Inconsistent data collection methods, diverse sensory panel protocols, and variable performance benchmarks hinder cross-study comparisons and cumulative knowledge building."
